  # ===========================================================================

  # Why: Core envelope construction — defines the wire format every gateway emits
  @task:TASK-FG-001
  @key-example @smoke @common @envelope
  Scenario: Building a command envelope from a user message
    Given a user message "How is the build going?"
    And the calling adapter is "openwebui"
    When I build a command envelope for the message
    Then the envelope should declare wire-format version "1.0"
    And the envelope should declare event type "command"
    And the envelope should identify the source as the OpenWebUI gateway
    And the envelope payload should carry the user's message text
    And the envelope should be tagged with a freshly generated correlation identifier

  # Why: Response unwrapping — the canonical happy-path response key
  @task:TASK-FG-001
  @key-example @smoke @common @envelope
  Scenario: Parsing a successful Jarvis response
    Given Jarvis has replied with the response text "Build complete"
    When I parse the result payload
    Then the parsed response should be "Build complete"

  # Why: End-to-end client behaviour — sending a command and receiving the answer
  @task:TASK-FG-002
  @key-example @smoke @common @jarvis-client
  Scenario: Sending a chat command to Jarvis and returning its reply
    Given a Jarvis client configured for the local NATS endpoint
    And Jarvis is ready to answer
    When I send the command "what is the fleet status?" through the client
    Then a command envelope should be published to the Jarvis command topic
    And the client should return Jarvis's reply text
    And the NATS connection should be released after the reply

  # Why: Hackathon-critical Graphiti read — Scholar's reason to exist
  @task:TASK-FG-003
