  # Why: Connection-per-call — overlapping requests must not share state
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] JarvisClient connects per call rather than holding a long-lived NATS connection across Pollen turns (scope §6 A5 mitigation)
  @task:TASK-FG-002
  @edge-case @common @jarvis-client
  Scenario: Concurrent JarvisClient calls do not share connection state
    Given a Jarvis client configured for the local NATS endpoint
    When two callers send commands through the client at the same time
    Then each call should establish its own NATS connection
    And each call should release its own connection after the reply
    And the two replies should not be cross-wired between the callers

